          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript with cover sheet, which describes the manuscript thus: "Haym Salomon Manuscript, in hand of a professional amanuensis, of Salomon's own account of the purchase of the property and the financing of the construction of Synagogue Mikveh Israel in 1782, including his own pledge of one-fourth the cost, 'Be it what it might.' Salomon describes the difficulties with Jonas Phillips which almost led to the latter's excommunication."
      
      Cover page indicates the manuscript is from the collection of Sigmund and Felicia Harrison of Ardmore, Pa.</summary>
